  "text": "6.4. The Drinfled-Sokolov reduction. Finally, we indicate that there exists another correspondence, close to the one we discussed here, which is called the Drinfeld-Sokolov reduction [DS] . This correspondence allows to construct W-algebras from Kac-Moody algebras. There is a Poisson isomorphism between the manifold of scalar differential operators of order n with the second Gelfand-Dickey bracket on one hand, and the manifold of matrix differential operators of order 1 viewed as a subspace of sl n * , with Kirillov-Kostant bracket on the other hand. The quantization of this correspondence is studied in [CITATION_1] . A q-deformed version of this correspondence, in which manifolds of differential operators are replaced by manifolds of q-difference operators is proposed in [FRS] and [SS] . Quantization of this correspondence leads to q-deformed W-algebra.",
